&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ISLE OF WIGHT NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Community Division&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;PHYSIOTHERAPY SERVICES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Msk, Chronic Pain, Orthopaedic Triage&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Specialist Physiotherapist Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;0.60 WTE (22.5 hrs)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Isle of Wight NHS Trust is offering an exciting opportunity for a currently senior Clinical Specialist Physiotherapist to join the Msk Physiotherapy Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post offers an opportunity for personal and professional development within an established service; supported by informed colleagues and assistants. The post seeks an enthusiastic applicant willing to develop the services integration with ED, Orthopaedics; MPTT; Rheumatology; Chronic Pain, Community Physiotherapists and Msk Occupational Health. Good initiative, interdisciplinary working and independent working are important elements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested applicants need to evidence: current senior level clinical practice within the Msk specialisms, HCPC registration, UK NHS experience and comprehensive post-graduate CPD within the specialism. Developing colleagues or students is part of the role as well as clinical/team leadership. Our service offers a commitment to supporting ongoing professional development as well as a supportive, friendly network of colleagues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Isle of Wight offers a great work/life balance for those interested in nature, culture and many outdoor activities/beaches. Traffic congestion is rare. There are good mainland transport links; many people commute between the island and the mainland and vice versa on a daily basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;If you would like to discuss this opportunity, please contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leeane Walsh, Principal Physiotherapist / (01983) 534376&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Kris Long, Msk Team Lead / (01983) 534219&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stuart Browne, Deputy Principal Physiotherapist / (01983) 534289&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
